The paper proposes a novel deep learning architecture for personalised point-of-interest (POI) recommendation, which involves capturing complicated user preferences and fine-grained user-POI relationships for spatio-temporal sensitive POI recommendation. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Information Retrieval (cs.IR) which deals with recommending relevant information to users, Machine Learning (cs.LG) which deals with developing algorithms that can learn from data, Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) which deals with modelling and analysing social networks, Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) which deals with natural language processing, and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) which deals with developing intelligent systems.
